\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.6}{\ignorespaces Comprehensive comparison of predecessor data structures. Variables: $k$ = set size, $b$ = significant bit positions, $u$ = universe size, $n$ = number of elements, $w$ = word size.}}{77}{}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.7}{\ignorespaces Practical space-time trade-offs. The improved Fredman method offers the best balance of speed and space efficiency for typical use cases.}}{78}{}%
